The Nigerian government has announced 12 new confirmed cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) in the country. The country’s lead agency, Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), disclosed this on its Twitter account Wednesday afternoon. It tweeted: “Twelve new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria; 9 in Osun, 2 in Edo and 1 in Ekiti State “As at 12:30 pm 1st April there are 151 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. Nine have been discharged with two deaths” Twelve new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria; 9 in Osun, 2 in Edo and 1 in Ekiti State As at 12:30 pm 1st April there are 151 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. Nine have been discharged with two deaths pic.twitter.com/SVxZ4H3pBd — NCDC (@NCDCgov) April 1, 2020  As at 12:30 pm 1st April, there are 151 confirmed cases
