Benue- 1 — NCDC (@NCDCgov) April 1, 2020  Surprisingly, Osun is recording more cases of the virus in Nigeria. Within the last 24 hours, the number of confirmed cases has moved from just two to 14 in the state. The NCDC had confirmed three new cases in the state on Tuesday afternoon and by Wednesday afternoon, another 9 was added. The Commissioner for Health in Osun, Dr Rafiu Isamotu, disclosed to Daily Trust in a chat on Tuesday that the five (now 14) persons confirmed to have contracted coronavirus in the state (as at Tuesday) were in stable condition. He said the isolation center at the State Specialist Hospital, Asubiaro in Osogbo, which has just been completed for the purpose, is well equipped with necessary facilities. Isamotu said the state has seven ventilators and that the situation was still under control. He advised the people of Osun State not to panic. COVID-19: Nigeria’s confirmed cases now 139 Coronavirus: Nigeria records 20 new cases, as total hits 131 COVID-19: Nigeria now has 44 cases